  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To improve child health through agroecological production and sanitation practices</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Fundacion Nuna will continue a new project cycle working with children on agroecology and young people on produce transformation in three municipalities in the La Paz department. The results of the baseline study in the previous project alongside the onset of the pandemic increased concerns about sanitation practices and lack of family infrastructure. In this new cycle, Nuna&#x2019;s team will broaden in scope to include training and materials to support improved awareness and implementation of safe sanitary practices, thereby improving child health in terms of both sanitation and nutrition. Nuna&#x2019;s commitment to recuperating indigenous knowledge, validating indigenous culture and practices and addressing gender inequality underpin their methodology and institutional approaches.</narrative>
  </description>
